        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 3 at 3:09PM PDT until June 3 at 4:00PM PDT by NWS Las Vegas NV</headline>
        <description>At 308 PM PDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over The Strip,
moving north at 10 mph. A spotter just west of the Las Vegas strip
reported quarter sized hail at 307 pm.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Las Vegas, Henderson, North Las Vegas, Summerlin, The Strip, Nellis
AFB, East Las Vegas, Sam Boyd Stadium, Spring Valley, Green Valley,
Enterprise, Fremont Street, Paradise, Mountains Edge, Lone Mountain,
Southern Highlands, Seven Hills, Silverado Ranch, Harry Reid
International Airport, and Las Vegas Ballpark.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
